ARAROMI community in Ondo State has felicitated with its Regent, Adeola Asaolu, on her 32nd birthday. Asaolu is daughter of the late Olu of Araromi – Olawale Omotayo. She was installed as regent on March 16 following his death.   Senator Arthur Nzeribe dies at 83     Buhari for Abidjan to attend COP-15     Wives of Vice-Chancellors postpone UNILAG conference   The community’s spokesperson, Pastor Kolawole Matthew, described the regent as a ‘kind, generous and wise ruler who has brought peace and development to the community’. He said: “Before she became regent, we had problems with electricity, but she helped to restore it. She promised to do more; building a palace, market, a borehole and help to revive primary education.”